phases.task:
Author-fold-in fixes suggested by review (not merge-blocking, but an honest author would fold them in):

{args.in-scope-fixes-json}

Approve = apply ALL. Edit = 'go minus 3,5' (skip some), 'adjust 2: <text>' (modify a fix), or 'skip' (apply none and proceed). Reject = stop.

FIX MODE — apply the user-approved fold-in fixes. Do NOT commit.

Worktree: {args.worktree-path}
Fold-in decision ('(approve)' = apply all, or an edit note): {steps.fold-in.output}

The in_scope_fixes list to choose from:
{args.in-scope-fixes-json}

Interpret the decision: '(approve)' = apply all; 'skip' = apply none; 'go minus <ids>' = apply all except those; 'adjust <id>: <text>' = apply that one with the modification. Output ONLY the fix-mode JSON result from your instructions.

Adversarial read-only verification review after fold-in fixes were applied.

Worktree: {args.worktree-path}
Branch: {args.branch}
Issue: {args.issue-json}
Base (diff against): {args.base}
Round: fold-in-verify

Output ONLY the JSON result from your instructions (merge_blockers, merge_blockers_count, in_scope_fixes, in_scope_fixes_count, findings).

CONSOLIDATE MODE — consolidate the out-of-scope `findings` into proposed triage issues (dedupe repeated patterns into single issues).

Findings from the review summary: {args.findings-json}
Findings from fold-in verification (may be empty if no fold-ins ran): {steps.fold-in-verify.json.findings}

Output ONLY the JSON from your consolidate mode (proposed_issues, consolidated_from_count).

Proposed triage issues from review findings:

{steps.triage.output}

Approve = create ALL proposed issues. Edit = 'create 1,3' (pick by index), 'drop 2' (exclude), or 'skip' (create none). Reject = stop.

CREATE MODE — create the approved triage issues via gh issue create. Repo: {args.repo} (empty = current repo).

Proposed issues: {steps.triage.output}
Approval decision ('(approve)' = create all, edit note = parse per your instructions, '(reject)' = create none): {steps.triage-approve.output}

Output ONLY the create-mode JSON result from your instructions.

Generate the self-contained HTML report for this issue's branch.

Issue JSON: {args.issue-json}
Branch: {args.branch}
Worktree: {args.worktree-path}
Base (diff against): {args.base}
Report directory: {args.report-path}

Read the issue number and title from the issue JSON. Output ONLY the JSON result from your instructions (including report_path).

Implementation complete. Report: {steps.reports.json.report_path}

{args.override-note}

Approve = merge into {args.base} and CONTINUE to the next issue. Edit = 'merge and stop' or 'stop without merging'. Reject = stop without merging.

MERGE MODE — perform the merge sequence for this issue.

Decision from the gate ('(approve)' = merge and continue, edit note = 'merge and stop' or 'stop without merging', '(reject)' = stop without merging): {steps.merge-approve.output}
Issue JSON: {args.issue-json}
Branch: {args.branch}
Worktree: {args.worktree-path}
Base: {args.base}
Test command (for post-conflict validation if needed): {args.test-command}
Report path (for regeneration if needed): {steps.reports.json.report_path}

If the decision is 'stop without merging', do NOT merge. If rebase conflicts arise, STOP and output the conflicts JSON. Otherwise complete commit/rebase/merge/cleanup. Output ONLY the merge-mode JSON from your instructions.

MERGE-RESUME MODE — the user resolved the rebase conflicts. Finish the sequence.

Issue JSON: {args.issue-json}
Branch: {args.branch}
Worktree: {args.worktree-path}
Base: {args.base}
Test command (re-run after resolution; if it fails, STOP and report tests_failed): {args.test-command}
Report path (regenerate): {steps.reports.json.report_path}

Continue the rebase, validate, regenerate the report, merge into base, clean up. Output ONLY the merge-resume JSON from your instructions.

Emit the final iteration result JSON so the outer skill knows how to proceed. The merge-resume output is empty if no conflicts occurred — ignore empty inputs.

Merge output: {steps.merge.output}
Merge-resume output: {steps.merge-resume.output}

Derive the decision ('merge and continue' | 'merge and stop' | 'stop without merging'). Output ONLY:
{"decision":"merge and continue|merge and stop|stop without merging","merged":true|false,"issue_number":N,"conflicts":false}

Do NOT run git commands — just read the outputs and emit JSON.
